hifiberry-configurator (2.13.20) stable; urgency=medium

  * config-txt: add USB gadget (OTG device) mode support -- new
    `config-txt --enable-usb-gadget` / `--disable-usb-gadget` CLI flags
    switch the dwc2 controller between peripheral and host mode, with
    model-aware config.txt section handling (CM5/Pi5 share a dwc2 node,
    CM4/Pi4 gate host mode via `otg_mode=`) so a change only ever touches
    a section the detected board actually reads.
  * config-txt: on Pi5/CM5, enabling USB gadget mode now also applies the
    PSU_MAX_CURRENT=3000 bootloader EEPROM workaround required for the
    gadget to enumerate on Apple hosts (new `booteeprom` module); a
    failed or unreadable EEPROM read is never treated as a value to
    apply, and the failure is logged as a warning rather than aborting
    the config.txt change.
  * config-txt: fix `otg_mode=` handling in `enable_usb_gadget` /
    `disable_usb_gadget` so it only touches the `[cm4]` section on an
    actual CM4 -- previously it was stripped unconditionally on every
    model, silently downgrading a Pi5/CM5 image later moved to a CM4
    from the stock XHCI host controller to dwc2's slower built-in host
    mode, with no restore path on disable.
  * release: bump to 2.13.20 -- 2.13.19 was already published from
    elsewhere without this USB gadget work, so this branch's build must
    not reuse that version number.

 -- HiFiBerry <info@hifiberry.com>  Wed, 15 Jul 2026 09:00:00 +0000

hifiberry-configurator (2.13.19) stable; urgency=medium

  * soundcard: detect input-only cards (the HiFiBerry ADC) from `arecord -l`.
    The ADC has no playback device, so it never appears in `aplay -l` and,
    without a HAT EEPROM or a `# HiFiBerry card:` pin, detection fell through
    to "Unknown" with 0 input channels — so `config-soundcard --has-input`
    wrongly reported no input on ADC boards configured via a raw
    `dtoverlay=hifiberry-adc`. Added an `arecord_contains` marker to the ADC
    card definition and an arecord detection step (after aplay, before DSP)
    that matches it, so the ADC is identified from its actual capture device.

