 -- HiFiBerry <info@hifiberry.com>  Mon, 06 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0000

hifiberry-configurator (2.13.16) stable; urgency=medium

  * debian: unify systemd unit handling under dh_installsystemd. The
    previous debian/rules used two dh_installsystemd calls, the second
    with --remaining-packages, which skips packages already processed in
    the same debhelper run (not units within a package) — so it was a
    no-op and only config-detect.service received dh-generated maintscript
    snippets. config-server.service (and the other units) therefore
    shipped without their multi-user.target.wants symlink on offline /
    chroot installs. Collapsed to a single dh_installsystemd call so the
    flags apply to every unit, and dropped the now-redundant hand-rolled
    systemctl enable/start (postinst) and stop/disable (prerm) blocks.
    Verified in an mmdebstrap arm64 Trixie chroot: all unit symlinks
    present, including config-server.service. (PR #6, mattias-arrelid)

  * debian/control: add missing runtime dependency on uuid. create-uuid
    .service runs /usr/bin/uuid > /etc/uuid, but /usr/bin/uuid is shipped
    by the uuid package (ossp-uuid), which was not declared as a
    dependency — only uuid-dev was pulled in transitively as a build-dep.
    On images where uuid was not otherwise installed, create-uuid.service
    failed at boot (status=127, /usr/bin/uuid: not found), leaving /etc/uuid
    absent. (PR #7, mattias-arrelid)

 -- HiFiBerry <info@hifiberry.com>  Tue, 16 Jun 2026 12:29:00 +0200

hifiberry-configurator (2.13.15) stable; urgency=medium

  * postinst: only touch systemd when it's actually running. The systemd
    block in debian/hifiberry-configurator.postinst now guards on
    [ -d /run/systemd/system ] in addition to the systemctl binary being
    present. In build chroots (rpi-image-gen, debootstrap, docker, pi-gen)
    systemctl exists but systemd is not PID 1, so `systemctl daemon-reload`
    failed with "System has not been booted with systemd as init system"
    and, under set -e, aborted the whole postinst — leaving the package
    unconfigured and cascading to dependents (hbos-minimal,
    hifiberry-shairport, hifiberry-mpd, hifiberry-librespot). This aligns
    hifiberry-configurator with the sibling packages (shairport, mpd,
    audiocontrol) that already guard the same way; behaviour on a real boot
    is unchanged. Fixes HBOS image builds with rpi-image-gen on Trixie.
    (PR #4, mattias-arrelid)

