hifiberry-configurator (2.13.14) stable; urgency=medium

  * SoundcardDetector: canonicalisation of card names through
    SOUND_CARD_DEFINITIONS aliases now runs centrally for ALL
    detection paths (HAT EEPROM, I2C probing, aplay, DSP detection),
    not just the HAT path that 2.13.13 covered. On a Beocreate Mk1
    HAT detection often returns nothing and I2C probing reports the
    short marketing name "Beocreate 4CA" — that's now canonicalised
    to "Beocreate 4-Channel Amplifier" before the result is returned,
    so the setup wizard's definition_found is True and the friendly
    "Detected sound card" panel shows up instead of the manual-browse
    fallback.

